markup.__html:
James Green, a prominent US scholar on Brazil and its civil-military dictatorship, spoke to Agência Pública on May 23rd about archived documents from the authoritarian regime and his perspective on the 2016 coup against Dilma Rousseff.

Commenting on the recently revealed CIA document about Ernesto Geisel, president of Brazil during the military regime, he says:
"the release of these documents indicates that Geisel violated human rights just as the other [authoritarian presidents] did, and that this was state policy."

Read the full interview in Portuguese in the link below, and take a look at Dr. Green's "Opening the Archives" initiative, a project to make publicly available US State Department documents from the dictatorship period: https://repository.library.brown.edu/studio/collections/id_644/

snapshot.caption: apublica.org
snapshot.link_description: Em visita a Porto Alegre, o pesquisador James Green, da Universidade Brown (EUA), fala do recém-descoberto telegrama de Geisel e da relação do governo americano com a ditadura brasileira
snapshot.title: Brasilianista busca revelações sobre ditadura em 100 mil documentos dos EUA

markup.__html:
משרד המשפטים מאמץ את המתווה אותו הציע Jerusalem Institute of Justice מכון ירושלים לצדק וקובע בצעד היסטורי - הטלת קנסות מנהליים על צרכני הזנות בישראל.
בהודעתה הערב מדגישה שרת המשפטים, איילת שקד, כי החוק מהווה בראש ובראשונה אמירה ערכית לדור הצעיר ולדור הנוכחי.

body_translations.en_XX:
The Ministry of Justice has officially adopted the proposed plan by the Jerusalem Institute of Justice מכון ירושלים לצדק to impose administrative #fines on the consumers of #prostitution in #Israel. This is a historic step indeed. 

During her address, Minister of Justice איילת שקד (Ayelet Shaked) noted that the law is first and foremost a statement for both the current, and younger generation.

markup.__html: Some 50,000 Venezuelans cross every day into Colombia in search of food, medical supplies, or a new life. They’re not fleeing war; they’re abandoning a failing state. As experts warn that President Nicolás Maduro’s election victory is likely to deepen the displacement crisis, IRIN contributor Magnus Boding Hansen travelled to the Colombian border to profile fleeing Venezuelans, with award-winning photographer Tomás Ayuso.

snapshot.caption: www.irinnews.org
snapshot.link_description: Venezuelans crossing into Colombia aren’t fleeing war; they’re abandoning a failing state
snapshot.title: Maduro election win is no victory for hungry Venezuelans
